		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65538926"><p><div class="quote"><p>So what you're saying is we have a risk that can't be closed in one way (paying), so we need to manage it by closing it a different way (backups / business continuity plans).</p><p>Hardening is the wrong approach. Step 1 is to have a disaster recovery plan, step 2 is to invest in preventing the disaster.</p></div><p>Why not all three? There are more nasty actors than just ransomware. Some of them want your data, but don't want you to know they have it.</p></div>
	</div>

